 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> you go</a>:=
</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Texas is taking steps that could cost BlackRoc=
k Inc., UBS Group AG and eight other finance firms business with the state =
after finding them to be hostile to the energy industry.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Glenn Hegar, the Republican state comptroller,=
 on Wednesday named the firms he considers to =E2=80=9Cboycott=E2=80=9D the=
 fossil fuel sector. The move ends roughly six months of suspense that led =
Texas municipal-bond issuers to avoid banks whose status was unclear amid t=
he office=E2=80=99s probe into companies=E2=80=99 energy policies. Governme=
ntal entities should use the list as a =E2=80=9Cfiltration system=E2=80=9D =
when entering contracts, Hegar said in an interview.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those firms disagree:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BlackRock, the world=E2=80=99s largest asset m=
anager, said in an emailed statement that the company disagrees with the co=
mptroller=E2=80=99s assessment.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThis is not a fact-based judgment,=E2=
=80=9D the statement said. =E2=80=9CBlackRock does not boycott fossil fuels=
 -- investing over $100 billion in Texas energy companies on behalf of our =
clients proves that. Elected and appointed public officials have a duty to =
act in the best interests of the people they serve. Politicizing state pens=
ion funds, restricting access to investments, and impacting the financial r=
eturns of retirees is not consistent with that duty.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A spokesperson for UBS said the company also d=
isagrees with the decision. =E2=80=9CWe provided their office with extensiv=
e information on our policies and practices, demonstrating that UBS does no=
t boycott energy companies even under a broad interpretation of Texas law,=
=E2=80=9D the statement said.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic issue here is that if you are an inv=
estment firm, and you decide not to invest in some particular oil company, =
Texas will send you a threatening letter saying =E2=80=9Cwe won=E2=80=99t d=
o business with people who boycott fossil fuels.=E2=80=9D And you will say =
=E2=80=9Cno, no boycott, we didn=E2=80=99t invest in that company because w=
e thought that the climate-related risks to its business were very high, so=
 as a pure valuation matter we thought it was a bad investment.=E2=80=9D An=
d Texas will say =E2=80=9Cno we think it=E2=80=99s because you don=E2=80=99=
t like oil companies.=E2=80=9D And you will send them a bunch of data and i=
nvesting memos and policy statements and legal analyses about how really yo=
u are only considering climate change as a financial matter, and they won=
=E2=80=99t believe you.=C2=A0We talked about this sort of thing yesterday. =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28846378.269571/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMjQvYW1jL=
XMtYXBlcy1taWdodC1zdGljay1hcm91bmQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDgyNTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRt=
X21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwODI1JnV0bV9=
jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3f129a6c" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> I wro=
te</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A certain amount of the ESG fight =
will take the form of broad public statements of principles. =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0But a lot of it will take the form (and has already taken the form) of f=
act-intensive debates about particular investment decisions. Some investmen=
t manager will say =E2=80=9Cwe are underweight oil and gas companies becaus=
e we are concerned about the financial impact of climate transition risk,=
=E2=80=9D and some state regulator will say =E2=80=9Cwe think it=E2=80=99s =
actually because you are environmentalists,=E2=80=9D and the investment man=
ager will say =E2=80=9Cno here is our investment model that considers envir=
onmental risk as a factor in assessing risk and returns,=E2=80=9D and the r=
egulator will say =E2=80=9Cwe think that you are using inappropriately long=
 investment horizons and imprudently weighting this risk in your calculatio=
n,=E2=80=9D and the manager will provide support for its view, and they=E2=
=80=99ll go back and forth. Every financial decision can also become a poli=
tical argument. It seems exhausting.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It still does.</p>
