<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I expressed some doubt about that, because the=
 thing about apes is that they don=E2=80=99t vote. AMC has tried before to =
get shareholder approval to issue more common stock, but it couldn=E2=80=99=
t. It would need a majority of all its outstanding shares to vote to approv=
e that, and that=E2=80=99s hard when 80% of its shares are held by retail i=
nvestors. I=C2=A0wrote:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">AMC stock is mostly held by retail=
 investors, and it is widely assumed that retail shareholders mostly don=E2=
=80=99t vote their stock. And in fact if you look at the results of AMC=E2=
=80=99s=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28846=
378.269571/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEv=
